    anchor: set-bg
    title: Set a custom background image
    body: |
        Make an image:

        - Ideally 3840 * 720 pixels. (Max 4096 * 2304.)
          - 578 pixels on either side will be covered by the "app launchers", with a transparency gradient, though you can [hide the passenger-side app launcher](#hide-passenger-launcher).
          - The wallpaper is split over two displays with a 60 pixel central black bar. ([Source](https://www.hondaeforums.com/viewtopic.php?p=4899#p4899).) If you want the appearance of the wallpaper continuing behind the bar, make a 3900 * 720 pixel image and crop out the middle 60 pixels.
        - Less than 10 MB.
        - BMP (`.bmp`) or JPEG (`.jpg`).
        - File name max 64 bytes long.

        You can use a ready-made template to get the dimensions right:

        - Adobe Photoshop
          - [Template](https://www.hondaeforums.com/viewtopic.php?p=5973#p5973) that doesn't account for the central bar.
          - [Template](https://www.hondaeforums.com/viewtopic.php?p=12978#p12978) that crops out the central bar.
        - Pixelmator Pro
          - [Template and AppleScript](https://www.hondaeforums.com/viewtopic.php?p=11087#p11087) that crop out the central bar.

        Put the image *at the root* of a USB drive.

        Connect the drive to the data-enabled front USB port (not the one with a battery icon).

        Go to General Settings > Display > Wallpaper to import or switch wallpaper.

        ([[manual 272–273]].)

        See [this forum thread](https://www.hondaeforums.com/viewtopic.php?t=255) for inspiration and ready-made images.

