    anchor: turn-off-climate-feedback
    title: Turn off the feedback display for climate controls
    body: |
        When you use climate controls, the screen will show an overlay for a few seconds, which can get in the way of e.g. satnav.

        To turn it off:

        1. Put the car into "ready to drive" mode.
        2. On the climate control system:
             - Turn the temperature down to "Lo".
             - Press "MODE" until it shows ![Air flows from floor and dashboard vents](/images/icon-vents.png).
             - Turn on ![](/images/icon-recirculation.png) recirculation.
             - Press "ON/OFF" to turn off the climate control system.
        3. Turn the car off.
        4. On the climate control system, press and hold both "MODE" and ![](/images/icon-recirculation.png) recirculation.
        5. While keeping the buttons pressed, put the car into "ready to drive" mode.
        6. The AC display should show "31.0". Keep the buttons pressed until it shows "19.0", then release them.

        To switch the feedback display back on, repeat the steps above, except:

        - In step 2, turn the temperature up to "Hi".
        - In step 6, wait for the display to show "31.0", then release the buttons.

        ([Source](https://www.hondaeforums.com/viewtopic.php?p=5435#p5435).)

